From Brian Kendig Subject Re Apr God's Promise in John Brian Ceccarelli writes Be warned it is not my job to convert That is the job of the Holy And I frankly make a lousy I am only here to Your conversion is between you and I am out of the loop If you decide to follow Jesus of which I indeed would be estatic then all the glory be to I've asked your god several times with all my heart to come to I really wish I could believe in him 'cos no matter how much confidence I build up on my own the universe is a big place and it would be so nice to know I have someone watching over me in I've gone into this with an open I've layed my beliefs aside from time to time when I've had doubt and I've prayed to see what good that would I don't see what more I can do to open myself to your god short of just deciding to believe for no good And if I decide to believe for no good reason why not believe in some other god Zeus seems like a pretty cool All I know is that in all my searching even though I've set aside my pride and decided that I want to know the truth no matter how difficult it may be to accept I have never had any encounter with any deity Christian or Please tell me what more I can do while still remaining true to Brian Kendig Je ne suis fait comme aucun de ceux que j'ai vus j'ose croire n'etre fait comme aucun de ceux qui The meaning of life Si je ne vaux pas mieux au moins je suis is that it Rousseau